+  - `src/pages/UserSetting/Mobile/Message/messagepageview.jsx`
+  - `src/pages/ListingPage/ListingMobileScreen.jsx`
+
+#### Shell Adoption and Structural Findings
+- Across the 37 unique route-owner files loaded by `AppRoutes.jsx`, only 8 currently use `BrandPageShell`, 3 use `StaticContentPage`, and 3 auth routes use `AuthLayout`; 24 route-owner files still import `Header` directly and 17 still import `Footer` directly.
+- `StaticContentPage.jsx` centralizes back-button and motion helpers, but it still renders `Header` and `Footer` itself instead of composing `BrandPageShell`, so even the already-data-driven static routes remain outside the shared Huz shell contract.
+- The public static backlog is still broad and mostly manual:
+  - `AboutUs`, `CoreValues`, `ComingSoon`, `FrequentlyAskedQuestions`, `TermsServices`, `PrivacyPolicy`, `ContactUs`, `VisaServices`, `HajjUmrahBusiness`, and `ListPackagePage` all bypass the shared branded shell.
+  - `TermsServices.jsx` is 1,324 lines and `PrivacyPolicy.jsx` is 642 lines, so these routes need template extraction that preserves exact copy and route stability instead of ad hoc JSX rewrites.
+- Content-family duplication is strong enough to support template-driven batches:
+  - `PreparationTips.jsx` and `TravelEssentials.jsx` are near-identical article pages with the same back-button, right-rail illustration, and related-articles section.
+  - `MadinahHolySites.jsx`, `JeddahHolySites.jsx`, and `TaifHolySites.jsx` share the same hero, `CityNavbar`, slider cards, and `AppDownload` footer rhythm; `MakkahHolySites.jsx` uses the same family shell with an extra tabbed data layer.
+- Protected account flow convergence is incomplete:
+  - `booking.jsx`, `paymentMethods.jsx`, and `PersonalDetailsPage.js` already align to the branded system.
+  - `bookingstatus.jsx`, `datatable.jsx`, `remainingPayment.jsx`, `operatorresponse.jsx`, `payment&wallet.jsx`, `messagePage.jsx`, and `wishlist.jsx` still render manual `Header` plus `SidebarMenu` shells instead of a shared responsive account shell.
+- Compatibility cleanup is partly finished but not closed:
+  - 9 mobile compatibility files remain under `src/pages`; 8 are one-line re-export wrappers.
+  - `src/pages/UserSetting/Mobile/Message/messagepageview.jsx` is still a standalone 278-line implementation and `rg` found no remaining imports from `src`, so it is a likely dead compatibility artifact.
+- Lead and partner pages still carry placeholder behavior:
+  - `VisaServices.jsx` and `ContactUs.jsx` submit to `console.log` only.
+  - `ListPackagePage.js` still uses a standalone operator-style hero and footer-only shell instead of the branded shared page system.
+
+#### Prioritized Execution Batches
+1. Batch A - Shared static foundation plus low-risk public info/legal routes:
+   - Build a `BrandPageShell`-backed static-page template layer and migrate `AboutUs`, `CoreValues`, `ComingSoon`, `FrequentlyAskedQuestions`, `TermsServices`, `PrivacyPolicy`, `PolicyPages`, and `GenericPages`.
+   - This is the highest-leverage batch because it removes the most repeated public-shell drift without touching booking/payment contracts.
+2. Batch B - Guide and holy-site content family:
+   - Consolidate `PreparationTips`, `TravelEssentials`, `UmrahGuide`, `MakkahHolySites`, `MadinahHolySites`, `JeddahHolySites`, and `TaifHolySites` onto reusable article and city-guide templates.
+   - Keep `HajjGuidance.jsx` as the reference route for branded public rhythm.
+3. Batch C - Lead-gen and partner pages:
+   - Bring `VisaServices`, `ContactUs`, `HajjUmrahBusiness`, and `ListPackagePage` onto the same branded shell and CTA language, while preserving existing outbound partner links and route stability.
+4. Batch D - Protected account shell convergence:
+   - Migrate `bookingstatus.jsx`, `datatable.jsx`, `remainingPayment.jsx`, `operatorresponse.jsx`, `payment&wallet.jsx`, `messagePage.jsx`, and `wishlist.jsx` to one reusable responsive account shell while preserving the current feature hooks and route handoff contracts.
+5. Batch E - Compatibility and dead-code cleanup:
+   - Remove or convert `messagepageview.jsx`, then audit the mobile re-export wrappers and protected alias routes after their canonical routes have been revalidated.
+
+#### Exact Next Batch Recommendation
+- Recommended next implementation batch: Batch A.
+- Batch A stays within the campaign limit of 8 pages, establishes the shared public-page primitives needed by later batches, avoids backend/API contract risk, and immediately aligns the most visible legal/info routes to the Huz shell contract.
+- Guardrails for Batch A:
+  - Preserve all existing route paths and legal copy.
+  - Keep `PolicyPages` and `GenericPages` data-driven.
+  - Do not run build or install commands; verify with route/import tracing and targeted content checks only.
+
